reviews.text: The famous level crossing gates no longer separate the posh resort part of Frinton from the so called Homelands now that they have been replaced by lifting barriers. But you can still see the old gates in the station car park where they were moved.

Clean and well kept station. A key transport gateway to the town.

The station is immediately to the west of a level crossing which provides road access to Frinton. The manually operated gates were replaced by a remotely controlled barrier in 2009 - causing much angst in the local community, who regarded the old gates akin a drawbridge protecting the town and inhabitants from ne're-do-wells.
Pretty substandard train station only really good for getting on train quickly nothing stands out about it wouldn't really recommend unless it's only option of train station
